U.K. Stocks Fluctuate as Drop in Banks Offsets Rally in Mining Companies

-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-08-09T12:46:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/u-k-stocks-fluctuate-as-drop-in-banks-offsets-rally-in-mining-companies.html
U.K. stocks fluctuated between gains
and losses as a selloff in banks offset a rebound in mining
companies.  The FTSE 100 Index rose 0.1 percent to 5,075.38 at 1:43
p.m. in  London  after earlier plunging as much as 5.5 percent and
rallying 1 percent. The gauge briefly fell 20 percent from its
high in February.  Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc dropped 6.5 percent to
25.48 pence, while Lloyds Banking Group Plc lost 2.8 percent to
31.9 pence. Antofagasta Plc rallied 5.2 percent to 1,195 pence
and Rio Tinto Group climbed 4.4 percent to 3,537 pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah Jones in London at 
